## PB3.1: bare resource capture is rejected at the M20g layer.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 31 (PB3 post-impl review): the PB3(1/5)
## audit's `is_capture_resource` flag is set ONLY for the
## explicit resource-mode captures `|+x|` / `|<x|` / `|~x|`.
## `cap_copy` (bare `|x|`) is intentionally EXCLUDED because
## M20g already rejects bare resource captures with a separate
## tailored diagnostic — the user is required to pick an
## explicit mode for any *T / ~T capture, which makes the
## refcount effect visible at the construction site (per Rig's
## visible-effects thesis).
##
## This example pins that invariant. If M20g's bare-resource-
## capture rejection ever weakens, the PB3 audit would silently
## fail to mark the binding as `is_capture_resource` and the
## body could consume the capture (UAF on multi-invocation).
## Keep this test green to keep the audit sound.

sub main()
  sig: *Signal(Int) = *Signal(value: 0)
  cb: *Closure() = *Closure(|sig| sig.get())
  cb()
